              }}></path></svg></span>{`Public Preview`}</h5></div><div parentName="div" {...{
        "className": "admonition-content"
      }}><p parentName="div">{`LiveData Migrator is in public preview. This gives you access to all product functionality for review, but limits operation time to 10 minutes during the preview period.`}</p></div></div>
    <p>{`Here, you'll find complete information about how to obtain and run LiveData Migrator.`}</p>
    <p>{`If you're new to the concept of LiveData, or want to know what LiveData Migrator does, please read the `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "/live-data-migrator/docs/"
      }}>{`introduction to LiveData Migrator`}</a>{` before learning how to install and use the product.`}</p>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "prerequisites"
    }}>{`Prerequisites`}</h2>
    <div {...{
      "className": "admonition admonition-info alert alert--info"
    }}><div parentName="div" {...{
        "className": "admonition-heading"
      }}><h5 parentName="div"><span parentName="h5" {...{
            "className": "admonition-icon"
          }}><svg parentName="span" {...{
              "xmlns": "http://www.w3.org/2000/svg",
              "width": "14",
              "height": "16",
              "viewBox": "0 0 14 16"
            }}><path parentName="svg" {...{
                "fillRule": "evenodd",
                "d": "M7 2.3c3.14 0 5.7 2.56 5.7 5.7s-2.56 5.7-5.7 5.7A5.71 5.71 0 0 1 1.3 8c0-3.14 2.56-5.7 5.7-5.7zM7 1C3.14 1 0 4.14 0 8s3.14 7 7 7 7-3.14 7-7-3.14-7-7-7zm1 3H6v5h2V4zm0 6H6v2h2v-2z"
              }}></path></svg></span>{`info`}</h5></div><div parentName="div" {...{
        "className": "admonition-content"
      }}><p parentName="div">{`The pre-requisites for running LiveData Migrator are simple, but differ based on your source environment. For production use, please ensure that all pre-requsities are satisfied before operating LiveData Migrator.`}</p></div></div>
    <ol>
      <li parentName="ol">{`A `}<strong parentName="li">{`Linux host`}</strong>{` running either Red Hat, Centos, Debian or Ubuntu, with a version that matches the requirements of your Hadoop cluster,`}</li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`If migrating from an HDFS source, your Linux host will need to be configured as an `}<strong parentName="li">{`edge node`}</strong>{` of the Hadoop cluster, giving it access to necessary Hadoop client libraries and configuration,`}</li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`When migrating from HDFS, you will need to be able to `}<strong parentName="li">{`authenticate`}</strong>{` as the `}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`hdfs`}</inlineCode>{` user if running from the command line,`}</li>
      <li parentName="ol"><strong parentName="li">{`Network connectivity`}</strong>{` from that host to your target storage endpoint if migrating to ADLS Gen 2, S3 or another Hadoop-compatible file system,`}</li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`Sufficient `}<strong parentName="li">{`network bandwidth`}</strong>{` to accommodate the transfer of existing data and ongoing changes, and`}</li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`If your HDFS source is in a secure (Kerberos-enabled) Hadoop cluster, you will need a `}<strong parentName="li">{`valid keytab file`}</strong>{` for the `}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`hdfs`}</inlineCode>{` user available on the Linux host.`}</li>
    </ol>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "recommendations"
    }}>{`Recommendations`}</h3>
    <ol>
      <li parentName="ol">{`We recommend a minimum of 100GB of `}<strong parentName="li">{`free disk space`}</strong>{`, more if you are expecting to migrate large files to cloud storage services because a temporary disk buffer will be used during migration,`}</li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`We also recommend `}<strong parentName="li">{`CPU and memory capacity`}</strong>{` on the host to support the processing needed for operation, which will be dominated by TLS encoding when transferring content to a remote target file system. Consider a modern 4-core VM instance type or physical machine, with 16GB of RAM or more as a base.`}</li>
    </ol>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "get-livedata-migrator"
    }}>{`Get LiveData Migrator`}</h2>
    <p>{`You can get LiveData Migrator during public preview using the WANdisco Customer Product Download portal. The current version is LiveData Migrator 1.1.1. WANdisco will update versions as the preview period continues.`}</p>
    <p>{`There are three files available, any one of which can be used to run LiveData Migrator:`}</p>
    <ul>
      <li parentName="ul">{`The `}<strong parentName="li">{`LiveData Migrator standalone Java archive`}</strong>{` (jar), which requires no installation process and is the fastest option to begin migration from the command line,`}</li>
      <li parentName="ul">{`The `}<strong parentName="li">{`RPM package`}</strong>{` that offers a system service for RPM-based Linux environments, and`}</li>
      <li parentName="ul">{`The `}<strong parentName="li">{`DEB package`}</strong>{` that offers the same system service for DEB-based Linux environments.`}</li>
    </ul>
    <p>{`Both of the Linux packages also contain the same Java archive that can also be used to run LiveData Migrator from the command line.`}</p>
    <div class="download">
      <a href="https://customer.wandisco.com">Download LiveData Migrator</a>
    </div>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "installation-files"
    }}>{`Installation Files`}</h3>
    <p>{`When LiveData Migrator is installed as a system service, the following directory locations are used:`}</p>
    <table>
      <thead parentName="table">
        <tr parentName="thead">
          <th parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`Location`}</th>
          <th parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`Content`}</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody parentName="table">
        <tr parentName="tbody">
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}><inlineCode parentName="td">{`/var/log/wandisco/live-migrator`}</inlineCode></td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`Log files created by LiveData Migrator during operation`}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr parentName="tbody">
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}><inlineCode parentName="td">{`/etc/wandisco/live-migrator`}</inlineCode></td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`Configuration files used by LiveData Migrator`}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr parentName="tbody">
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}><inlineCode parentName="td">{`/opt/wandisco/live-migrator`}</inlineCode></td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`Java archive files for LiveData Migrator`}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr parentName="tbody">
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}><inlineCode parentName="td">{`/opt/wandisco/live-migrator/db`}</inlineCode></td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": null
          }}>{`LiveData Migrator runtime state`}</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "running-livedata-migrator"
    }}>{`Running LiveData Migrator`}</h2>
    <p>{`You have two options for running LiveData Migrator:`}</p>
    <ul>
      <li parentName="ul">{`from the `}<em parentName="li">{`command line`}</em>{`, or`}</li>
      <li parentName="ul">{`as a `}<em parentName="li">{`system service`}</em>{`.`}</li>
    </ul>
    <p>{`You only need to install the product if you want to run it as a system service, which allows you to maintain long-lived migrations, have a common configuration that survives service restarts, and to retain logging information in a central directory. Running LiveData Migrator from the command line allows you to get started with migration in just a few seconds, and does not need any special local system privileges to operate.`}</p>
