              }}></path></svg></span>{`note`}</h5></div><div parentName="div" {...{
        "className": "admonition-content"
      }}><p parentName="div">{`You will need to define an HDFS file system resource using the `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`--source`}</inlineCode>{` parameter on the `}<a parentName="p" {...{
            "href": "/live-data-migrator/docs/command-reference#filesystem-add-hdfs"
          }}><inlineCode parentName="a">{`filesystem add hdfs`}</inlineCode></a>{` command to create a suitable HDFS source file system when running as a system service.`}</p></div></div>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "running-in-secure-environments"
    }}>{`Running in Secure Environments`}</h2>
    <p>{`Hadoop can run in a secure mode that uses Kerberos to authenticate users and applications. LiveData Migrator can be configured easily to operate with Kerberos security.`}</p>
    <p>{`When run from the command line, LiveData Migrator will use the initial ticket-granting ticket for a principal obtained by previous execution of `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`kinit`}</inlineCode>{`:`}</p>
    <ol>
      <li parentName="ol">{`Login to a system shell as the user that will run LiveData Migrator,`}</li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`Execute the `}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`kinit`}</inlineCode>{` command to obtain a Kerberos ticket-granting ticket, then`}</li>
      <li parentName="ol"><a parentName="li" {...{
          "href": "#option-1-command-line-operation"
        }}>{`Run LiveData Migrator from the command-line`}</a>{`.`}</li>
    </ol>
    <p>{`When run as a system service, LiveData Migrator will honor the `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "/live-data-migrator/docs/configuration#kerberos-integration"
      }}>{`configuration for Kerberos security`}</a>{` in `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`application.properties`}</inlineCode>{`.`}</p>
    <ol>
      <li parentName="ol">{`Configure your Kerberos security to accept credentials in a keytab file available to the user identity that will be used to run LiveData Migrator (typically the `}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`hdfs`}</inlineCode>{` user)`}</li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`Configure LiveData migrator properties for Kerberos integration, then`}</li>
      <li parentName="ol"><a parentName="li" {...{
          "href": "#option-2-system-service-installation"
        }}>{`Run LiveData Migrator as a system service`}</a>{`.`}</li>
    </ol>
    <h1 {...{
      "id": "livedata-migrator-operation"
    }}>{`LiveData Migrator Operation`}</h1>
    <p>{`Once you have LiveData Migrator running, you will `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "/live-data-migrator/docs/operation"
      }}>{`interact with the action prompt`}</a>{` to configure, manage and monitor resources that control how your migration takes place.`}</p>
    </MDXLayout>;
}

